I've split the giant FitAllHistos.C macro into three smaller ones. 
This makes the analysis much easier to run and avoids generating unnecessary output (for example, if I only need the .txt file
with the p1 and err_p1 values, I don't need to generate the multigraphs).
The only constraint is that the macros must be run in this specific order:
1. FitPeaks.C: Creates the Gaussian fit plots on the charge histograms.
2. ExtractGains.C: Creates the .txt file with p1 and its error, and saves the p1 plot.
3. PlotMultiGraph.C: Opens the .root file created in step 1 and filters the good/bad p1 values saved in step 2.
A final note: All the code comes from our original FitAllHistos.C. For the third macro, I didn't integrate Caterina's recent 
improvements from the last lab session. Once she pushes her updates to GitHub, I will update this macro accordingly.
